continue is a Java keyword. It skips the remainder of the loop and continues with the next iteration.For example:int maxLoopIter = 7;

for (int i = 0; i < maxLoopIter; i++ ) {
   if (i == 5) {
      continue;  // -- 5 iteration is skipped --
   }
   System.println("Iteration = " + i);
